        &lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.leafony.com/en/docs/leaf/communication/ac03/&#34;&gt;LoRa Easy leaf&lt;/a&gt;, sensor data (temperature, humidity, illumination, tilt) can be sent to a distant location and output to a PC terminal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;LoRa_receiver_sender.png&#34; width=500&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is a discrepancy between the temperature (or humidity) you want to display and the temperature (or humidity) of the 4-Sensors, perform the correction between the two points. For details, see &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.leafony.com/en/docs/examples/beginner/1_p/basic/temp_humid_sensors/#two-point_correction&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;demo-video&#34;&gt;Demo Video&lt;/h2&gt;
