&lt;h2 id=&#34;assembly&#34;&gt;Assembly&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assemble the leaves as shown in the figure below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;sending-side&#34;&gt;Sending side&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;./LoRa_sender_assemble.png&#34; alt=&#34;assemble1&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;receiving-side&#34;&gt;Receiving side&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;./LoRa_receiver_assemble.png&#34; alt=&#34;assemble2&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;source-code&#34;&gt;Source code&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-Sensors and AVR MCU library (timer interrupt) are required for writing. Please include the library beforehand. For details, see &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.leafony.com/en/docs/environment/avr/arduino/&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the Arduino IDE, write the following program.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sending side &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Leafony/Sample-Sketches/blob/master/LoRa/4-Sensors_LoRa_Tx.ino&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;4-Sensors_LoRa_Tx.ino&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receiving side &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Leafony/Sample-Sketches/blob/master/LoRa/LoRa_Rx_Serial_monitor.ino&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;LoRa_Rx_Serial_monitor.ino&lt;/a&gt;
　&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;execution-result&#34;&gt;Execution result&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open the serial monitor in the Arduino IDE and set the baud rate to 9600 bps to display the sensor data (temperature, humidity, illumination, and tilt).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;LoRa.png&#34; width=&#34;450&#34;&gt;
